# Implementation Plan - AI-Powered Student Recruitment Platform

Build a modern, responsive, and highly interactive recruitment platform designed for students (Job Seekers) and recruiters, utilizing a Node.js + Express backend and a React (Vite) frontend.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Database Selection:** We will use SQLite via Sequelize for local development. SQLite requires no local database service installation and stores data in a file (`database.sqlite`). The schema is fully compatible with PostgreSQL and can be switched by changing connection strings in the `.env` file.
> 
> **File Uploads & Resume Parsing:** For MVP stability, file uploads will write to a local `uploads/` directory on the server (simulating Cloudinary), and we will provide mock resume parsing/parsing simulation that evaluates uploaded PDFs.
> 
> **AI Integrations:** For the MVP, we will simulate the AI responses (Resume Analysis, GitHub Code Quality, Career Coach, and Profile Verification) using modular service layers in the backend. These mock services will generate dynamic scores and descriptions but are structured so that they can be easily replaced with OpenAI, Gemini, or Anthropic API calls.

## Proposed Changes

We will organize the application into a mono-repo structure in the workspace:
- `/backend`: Node.js, Express, Sequelize (SQLite), JWT authentication, local uploads, mock AI services.
- `/frontend`: React (Vite), Vanilla CSS (glassmorphism/dark mode/animations), Lucide icons, custom interactive SVG/CSS charts.

